# Forms (Required)

Use `react-hook-form` for state. **Never** build one-off field wrappers — use `FormCommon` from `@/components/common/FormCommon`.

```tsx
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { FormCommon, Input, Select } from "@/components/common/FormCommon";

const form = useForm<FormValues>({ defaultValues: { … } });

<FormCommon form={form} onSubmit={onSubmit}>
  <Input control={form.control} name="email" label="Email" required />
  <Select control={form.control} name="role" label="Role" options={…} />
</FormCommon>
```

**Available fields:** `Input`, `Textarea`, `Select`, `RadioGroup`, `Checkbox`, `DatePicker`, `ImagePicker`.

- Pass `control`, `name`, `label`; use `required` for required fields.
- Labels/descriptions use `Typography` internally — don't add raw labels.
- Need a new field type? Extend `FormCommon.tsx`, don't duplicate elsewhere.
- Missing `@/components/ui/form`? Install via shadcn — FormCommon depends on it.
